<br>
The best way they could have fixed it was to make all loot no drop and return the lore tags back to only quest related items, as to how it was originally at release. Lore tags were originally created to signify that an item was related to a quest. It was said that approximately 60 percent of all quests that were implemented at release and still in play are unsolved. <br>
<br>
When people started farming in the beginning at release, they implemented lore tags on all items across the board. The farming was so bad, you were seeing wizards in upper guk with an entire bag of ghoulbane swords and selling them. <br>
<br>
While their decision was wonderful to stop the kill stealing, it killed questing in a major way. Ever wonder how many of those items that you think are loot actually are pieces of a puzzle to some unfinished quest? Makes you wonder.<br>
<br>
By having all loot no drop all down the board, I think it really kills alot of the &quot;loot aspect&quot; that causes alot of the problems, farming, etc etc etc. Think about it, they made the lore tags just to stop farming. Wouldn't make a whole lot of sense to for a wizard to loot something thats no drop that he can't sell, or anyone else for that matter.<br>
<br>
I know someone might say &quot;well what about the Economy?&quot;. Economy in a ROLE PLAYING game is WRONG. Why? I know many here have played table top role playing games, which EQ was originaly designated to emulate in a multi player setting. In any table top game, when oh when oh when did a DM/GM ever have a working economy? He didn't. You also don't have &quot;magic shops&quot; where you could go buy holy swords, ungodly magic items, and other relics of great power.<br>
<br>
Having everything no drop I think would really help on a positive fact for community level as well. Think about that piece of loot you can't grab so you shout and offer it up to the first person thats nearby, and you just helped someone out. One final note, no matter how you try and handle an &quot;economy&quot;...sooner or later it bottoms out, and over enough time...everyone has everything. You can't avoid it. It's all just a matter of time. <p>Banegrivm Shadowblight<br>Sovereign Lord of the <a href=http://www.1stfistoflight.com>1st Fist of Light</a><br></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showPrevMessage?topicID=1616.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showNextMessage?topicID=1616.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1616.topic&index=3><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.threadControl?topicID=1616.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1616.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1616.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub94.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump t